									<h3>About me</h3>
						<!--		</div>	-->					   
									
								<!--	<img class="featuredImg" src="img/IMG_1037.JPG" width="100%">	-->					   
<p>I'm a UX Designer at WebStart Bristol based at the Engine Shed Incubator. I do freelance projects and currently I'm designing and building websites for a range of businesses that include a catering, a natural beauty products, and a registered 'not for profit' company providing computer networking services and training. I enjoy being highly creative, keeping up-to-date with designing. I'm a member and regularly attend talks/meet-ups of local 'tech' groups. Love everything creative and when I'm not in front of a computer, I can be found beavering away at my allotment.</p> 
<p>My experience in designing for user experience/usability includes:</p> 
				<div class="left_list_experience_two_columns">
					<ul>
    					<li>Wireframing</li>
	      			<li>Designing the Information Architecture</li> 
	      			<li>Expert Heuristic & User-based Evaluations</li>
	      			<li>Co-Design</li>
	      			<li>Persona development</li>
    				</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="right_list_experience_two_columns">
    				<ul>
       				<li>Task Analysis</li> 
	      			<li>Usability Testing/Research and Analysis</li>
	      			<li>Fieldwork Observations</li> 
	      			<li>Interviewing</li>
	      			<li>Remote User Testing</li> 
    				</ul>
				</div>	
<p>I co-run a local UX/Usability group, organising the monthly free to attend talks from local companies/individuals on a wide-range of UX design/Usability topics with the aim of a community that regularly shares experience and knowledge.</p>

<p>Use Java, Python programming languages; My SQL; Server side: LAMP; Web development: Ruby on Rails, JavaScript, JQuery, HTML5, CSS3, Drupal 7, although I'm adaptable to all problem-solving.</p>

<p>Co-ordinated/organised the Bristol ITMegaMeet 2013 (June 2013) for which over 300 people registered, and an organiser for this annual event. http://bristol.itmegameet.co.uk</p>

<p>Completed an MSc (merit) Software Development (IT) degree at UWE, including a UWE internship completing research in Persuasive Design, as well as designing for usability/usability testing for older adults working as a UWE intern on the MOBISERV research project at the BRL (Bristol Robotics Laboratory). http://www.brl.ac.uk/researchprojects/mobiservproject.aspx</p>
